Cpu / Turbo Parameters IA Clip Reason

Comments +

Normal behavior:
1. CPU IA is unlimited without Prochot event
2. CPU IA is unlimited without Thermal event
3. CPU IA is unlimited without VR Thermal Alert event
4. CPU IA is unlimited without VR protected event

Warning behavior:
5. CPU IA is limited with Thermal event and reduce CPU IA core clock frequency adaptively until the TCC is de-activated
6. CPU IA is limited with VR Thermal Alert event and reduce CPU IA core clock frequency gradually to NominalTDPFrequency
7. CPU IA is limited with VR protected event and Limited CPU IA core clock frequency on TDC Power Limit

Critical behavior:
8. CPU IA is limited with Prochot event and reduce CPU IA core clock frequency rapidly to the LFM frequency.
. Not Clipped: 0; Prochot: 1; Thermal Event: 2; VR Thermal Alert: 3; PBM_PL1: 4; VR_TDC: 5; MAX_TURBO_LIMIT: 6; Other (IccMax/PL4/etc);MAX_TURBO_LIMIT: 7; Other (IccMax/PL4/etc): 8; Other (IccMax/PL4/etc);PBM_PL2: 9; PBM_PL2: 10; Thermal Event;MAX_TURBO_LIMIT: 11

Cpu / Throttling

Comments +

Normal behavior:

Warning behavior:
2. CPU IA is limited with Throttling event and CPU IA core clock frequency adaptively until the TCC is de-activated

Cpu / Turbo Capability

Comments +

Normal behavior:

Critical behavior:

. Supported and Enabled: 0

Comments +

Debug Tips:
Compare Power Metric between higher CPU IA Performance and lower CPU IA Performance
On same test scenario with below tips
1. If CPU Power Limit are same
* Turbo Parameters-MSR Power Limit_1 Power(Watts)
* Turbo Parameters-MSR Power Limit_2 Power(Watts)
* Turbo Parameters-MSR Power Limit_4 Power(Watts)
* Turbo Parameters-MMIO Power Limit_1 Power(Watts)
* Turbo Parameters-MMIO Power Limit_2 Power(Watts)
* Turbo Parameters-MSR Power Limit_1 Time(Seconds)
* Turbo Parameters-MMIO Power Limit_1 Time(Seconds)
2. If turbo duration are similar by EWMA value on turbo state
* Idle Package Power decide initial EWMA value: lower idle package power, lower initial EWMA Value
* Power Limit_1 Time (Tau) decide EWMA ramp speed: larger Tau parameter cause EWMA power to ramp slower
* Power Limit_2 limited Turbo Package Power: lower turbo package power with lower Power Limit_2 can keep lower EWMA power, and keep longer turbo duration.
* Power Limit_1 decide EWMA threshold: higher Power Limit_1 keep longer turbo duration
* Budget(t)=PL1-EWMA(t), If Budget <= 0, exits Turbo
EWMA(t)=EWMA(t-1) + (1/Tau)*(P(t)-EWMA(t-1))
EWMA(0)=P(idle)
* P(t) < PL2
3. If line charts of main CPU power metric are similar: IA Power-> Rest of Package/GT Power -> Package Power
4. If average values of main CPU power metric are similar: IA Power-> Rest of Package/GT Power -> Package Power
5. Focus on below typical cause:
IA Power gap is caused by Rest of Package
6. If there are prochot and thermal events during turbo state by Turbo Parameters IA Clip Reason
* Prochot / * Thermal Event / * VR Thermal Alert / * VR_TDC
.

Cpu / Frequency

Comments +

If Thermal Event happened, CPUn-Frequency would drop adaptively until the TCC is de-activated.
If Prochot happened, CPUn-Frequency would drop to CPU-Info-LFM(MHz) until the system de-asserts PROCHOT#.
If thermal control Turbo Off happened, CPUn-Frequency would drop to NominalTDPFrequency until turbo resumed.
If PLx setting dynamically changed, CPUn-Frequency would change adaptively..

IGFX / Turbo Parameters Gt Clip Reason

Comments +

Normal behavior:
1. CPU GT is unlimited without Prochot event
2. CPU GT is unlimited without Thermal event
3. CPU GT is unlimited without VR Thermal Alert event
4. CPU GT is unlimited without VR protected event

Warning behavior:
5. CPU GT is limited with Thermal event and reduce CPU GT core clock frequency adaptively until the TCC is de-activated
6. CPU GT is limited with VR Thermal Alert event and reduce CPU GT core clock frequency gradually until VR Thermal Alert event disappear
7. CPU GT is limited with VR protected event and Limited CPU GT core clock frequency on TDC Power Limit

Critical behavior:
8. CPU GT is limited with Prochot event and reduce CPU GT core clock frequency rapidly to the LFM frequency.
. Not Clipped: 0; Prochot: 1; Thermal Event: 2; VR Thermal Alert: 3; PBM_PL1: 4; VR_TDC: 5; PBM_PL2: 6; VR_TDC;PBM_PL2: 7
